-- Hyundai Motor aims to lift U.S. sales by 4 percent in 2013
-- 
-- Thu Jan 24, 2013 12:42am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/24/us-hyundai-idUSBRE90N05H20130124

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - South Korean automaker Hyundai Motor ( 005380.KS ) aims to increase its U.S. sales by 4.4 percent to 734,000 vehicles this year from last year, in line with the market's growth, its chief financial officer Lee Won-hee said on Thursday. 
 Hyundai, which boosted sales in Europe last year, expected its sales to fall 6.5 percent in the region, while its China sales are forecast to jump 13.3 percent, Lee said during an earnings conference call. (Reporting by Hyunjoo Jin; Editing by Jacqueline Wong)